The paper deals with low-density parity-check codes, which are commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.CC) communities. The focus on trapping sets and girths suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the graph theory and combinatorics (cs.DS) community. The use of exponent matrices and lifting degrees suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the signal processing (cs.SI) and networking (cs.NI) communities.
